he possibilities of breaking the cycle of negative consequences that result from the inability to deal with guilt. Leeb shows us that only by guilt can individuals and nations take responsibility for their past crimes, show solidarity with the victims of crimes, and prevent the emergence of new crimes.Find out moreRead Claudia Leeb's interview with WINA Magazin (in German)"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGuiltxPolitical aspects. 0aGuiltzAustria. 0aPsychoanalysis. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xAtrocitiesxPsychological aspects. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xMoral and ethical aspectszAustria. 4aPolitics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831107804370 cprintz978147441324440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474413251?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474413251423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474413251/original  a978-3-11-078043-7  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK